column1: EHS_CO_Provider Details and Billing Details are wrong
column13:
*Issue -*

*Biller amount should be Write off or 0$ and Provider Details should be given as in Ready Set*

*2) Verify the Health ConnectÂ whether the Order is created*

*Biller amount is 67.2$ and Provider Details is NOT as given as in Ready Set*

column1: EHS_CO_In cerner the status is not reflecting as completed
column13:
*Issue: EHS_CO In cerner the status is not reflecting as completed*Â 

*Steps to Reproduce -*Â 

1) Login to Ready Set for Colorado Region with a MRN

2) Select the Varicella Lab order

3) Select the order

4) Assign to above tests

5) Order the selected tests

6) Login to KPHC for the same MRN and verify the order with order present with the status as blank

7) Login to Cerner with the same MRN

8) Navigate to the Result Entry to find the orderables is present

9) Navigate to the collections Enquiry

10) Navigate to the View -> Select Template

11) Select the CO template

12) Enter the MRN and click on SearchÂ 

13) Select the MRN and select the labels as zzzlabel

14) click on Label

15) Select the Order with all label types, Select the location as RRL CPÂ 

16) Click on Print

17) Status in Cerner changed to Dispatched

18) Select the Order and navigate to the Specimen Login

19) Click on Login to complete the Specimen Login

20)Â Status in Cerner changed to In-Lab and KPHC changed as In Process.Â 

21)Â Select the Order and navigate to the Results Entry

22) There are 2 drop downs present.Â 

23) Select values in the order and click on Verify

Actual results: In cerner after result entry the status is changing to In process

Expected results:after result entry the status should reflet as completed

column1: EHS_CO_Timestamps are shown as only 10:00 PM in Cerner for Scheduled, Pending, Cancelled and Dispatched Status
column13:
Â 

Issue -Â 

EHS_CO_Could not Complete the Vericella Orderables

Steps to Reproduce -Â 

1) Login to Ready Set for Colorado Region with a MRN

2) Select the Varicella Lab order

3) Select the order

4) Assign to above tests

5) Order the selected tests

6) Login to KPHC for the same MRN and verify the order with order present with the status as blank

7) Login to Cerner with the same MRN

8) Navigate to the Result Entry to find the orderable is present (Verify the TimeStamp Ã¨ Time Stamp shows as 10:00 pm)

9) Navigate to the collections Enquiry

10) Navigate to the View -> Select Template

11) Select the CO template

12) Enter the MRN and click on SearchÂ 

13) Select the MRN and select the labels as zzzlabel (Verify the TimeStamp Ã¨ Time Stamp shows as 10:00 pm)

14) click on Label

15) Select the Order with all label types, Select the location as RRL CPÂ 

16) Click on Print

17) Status in Cerner changed to Dispatched (Verify the TimeStamp Ã¨ Time Stamp shows as 10:00 pm)

18) Select the Order and navigate to the Specimen Login (Verify the TimeStamp Ã¨ Time Stamp shows as 10:00 pm)

19) Click on Login to complete the Specimen Login

20)Â Status in Cerner changed to In-Lab and KPHC changed as In Process.Â 

21)Â Select the Order and navigate to the Results Entry (Verify the TimeStamp Ã¨ Time Stamp shows as 3:43 am which is actual time)

*Expected results -*Â 

Time Stamp in Cerner for all the status like In Lab, Pending, Scheduled, Dispatched, In Process, Canceled & CompletedÂ should be the actual time in which we sent the order from the Ready Set. Â 

*Actual results -*Â 

Time Stamp in Cerner for all the status like In Lab, Pending, Scheduled, Dispatched, In Process, Canceled & CompletedÂ is NOT the actual time in which we sent the order from the Ready Set.
|Cerner Status|Time Stamp|
|Scheduled|10:00 PM|
|Pending|10:00 PM|
|Dispatched|10:00 PM|
|In Process|3:43 AM (Actual Time)|
|Cancelled|10:00 PM|
|In lab|3:43 AM (Actual Time)|
|Completed|3:43 AM (Actual Time)|

column1: FUTURE RELEASE: Update Clarity Immunization Report to include additional labs

Hep B surface antibody 
	Hep B surface antigen 
	Hep B core antibody
	Heb C virus antibody
	Measles, mumps, rubella, varicella IgG (immunity titers)
	Hepatitis a IgG (immunity titer)

column1: EHS Lab and Radiology orders Interfaces are stopped, and the order placed in Readyset haven't reached KPHC.
column13:
Issue :
EHS Lab and Radiology orders Interfaces are stopped, and the order placed in Readyset haven't reached KPHC.
Steps to reproduce :
Login to Resadyset.
Click on the EHS Manager Tab
Select the patient from the Participant Management Tab
Select the Lab Order IGRA or TSPOT- QFTB GOLD from the Order Tests Tab
Click order selected tests to place the lab order
Login to KPHC and Search with the Same MRN.
Navigate to Interface monitor.
Select the Definition name in the definition select pop up.
Verify whether the EHS lab & Radiology Order interfaces are running.

Actual Result :
EHS Lab and Radiology orders Interfaces are stopped, and the order placed in Readyset haven't reached KPHC.

Expected Result :
EHS Lab and Radiology orders Interfaces should not stopped, and the order placed in Readyset should be reached KPHC.

column1: Complete ServiceNow intake - EHS
column13:
The first step is to create a ServiceNow [Directed Service Request|https://xxxxx.xxx.service-now.com/sp?id=sc_cat_item&sys_id=b7409ba5dbe70f4003129c94db9619d8] (DSR) to CDTS ATLAS RPM Portfolio Management. In that request, identify the following:

Â 
 # Request to establish new ABC ID in RPM and corresponding ATLAS Record
 # Schedule session to identify and add in required information into the ATLAS Record

Â 

Once you have the ATLAS Record and ABC ID, go to ASG's [FastTrack|https://solutions.sp.xxxxx.xxx/services/asg/fastrack/SitePages/fastrack.aspx] and request an AIA.

Â 

As the Go-Live date approaches, create a second DSR to CDTS ATLAS RPM Portfolio Management to update the planned go-live date along with any changes. This may also include moving the record from planning to production. Please note, a the Configuration Item (CI), synonymous with the application full name in ATLAS, will not appear in ServiceNow until the application is moved to active status (note below). Â 

Â 

Once the record is identified as being prepared for production, go to ServiceNow and create an [EngageIT|https://xxxxx.xxx.service-now.com/sp?id=sc_cat_item&sys_id=4bb7ca2bdb8f0f001588753a8c9619e7] Request using the service requested as "ServiceNow" to identify the CAB Routing and Incident Routing of the application (Configuration Item). The CI routing will be your application name and the group information will be the group name that is provided by the support organization. If this is ASG for example, your ASG Intake specialist should provide you this group name. The CAB routing is manually completed as of March 2019, but is eventually going to become automated. For now, I would recommended consulting Enterprise Change Management ([http://chgmgmt.appl.xxxxx.xxx/wp/]) for proper routing. Contact suggestions are [@Alan D Prochaska|mailto:Alan.D.Prochaska@xxxxx.xxx] and [@Patricia M. Justice|mailto:patricia.m.justice@xxxxx.xxx]. They can help you identify the correct CAB.

column13:
As a Kaiser Manager, Supervisor, etc., I WANT TO pull employee annuals / surveillance reports SO THAT I can ensure compliance for my staff and eliminate potential fines or missed work due to non-compliance.

Â 

As an EHS staff member,Â I WANT TO access and/or build custom reports which vary by regional need and include reports such as OSHA 300, Surveillance, compliance by department / unit, track exposure by employee, EH screenings done by other EH departments (employee transfers), SO THAT I can focus on reducing manual report building, risk, and re-testing due to not having this data in one location which is easily accessible ad-hoc.

column1: HR to EHS interface for employee demographic data
column13:
Â 

As an EHS staff member,Â I WANT TO receive HR Employee demographic data into the EHS EMR which triggers new employee workflows and automates updates to employee demographics data, SO THAT I can be proactive in onboarding new employees, reducing manual and duplicative data entry, reducing risk, time, and effort of working in multiple systems in order to streamline the onboarding process and automate changes in demographic information.

column1: Epic to EHS interface for placing orders and receiving order results
column13:
As a Kaiser Employee / Physician / Volunteer / etc., I WANT TO view and print my EHS record, comply with myÂ annual screening / vaccinationÂ requirements paperwork (and scheduling) online; SO THAT I can ensure I am compliant to continue working in a patient care environment.Â 

Â 

As an EHS staff member,Â I WANT TO place orders in our EHS EMR for pre-screening, annuals (flu, tb, etc) and receive order results back in the EHS EMR, SO THAT I have visibility into an employee medical record from one system, eliminating risk, time, and effort of working in multiple systems. I will also lower the risk of being non-compliant by accessing medical history data stored in Epic (HealthConnect) that is not considered Employee data and vice versa.Â
